        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 7:38PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 737 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Saco, or 16 miles northeast of Malta, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vandalia, Bowdoin, Tampico, Sleeping Buffalo, Saco, and Hinsdale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
